{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 14:24:51.037595", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Solution submitted.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"server_access_router\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"ospf_area_misconfiguration\"]\n\nRationale (brief):\n- The server_access_router advertises 10.200.0.0/24 into OSPF (network 10.200.0.0/24 area 0), which causes core routers to install routes to the backend web servers, enabling direct reachability from user subnets. This violates the design requirement that backends be reachable only via the load balancer. The issue is classified as an OSPF area/advertisement misconfiguration.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2217, "output_tokens": 137, "total_tokens": 2354, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
